This page is the General Overview section of the dashboard. If the Home Page was the "front door," this page is the "Big Picture" summary where you can see the hospital's most important numbers all in one place.

Here is what this page shows you in simple terms:

1. The "Quick Stats" (The Big Numbers)
At the top, you’ll see several large numbers. These are the most important facts for the day, such as:

Total Patients: Exactly how many people are being treated.

Available Beds: A critical number that tells staff if they can accept more patients.

Doctors on Duty: How many medical professionals are currently working.

2. Admissions vs. Discharges (The "In and Out")
There is likely a chart here that acts like a scale. It shows how many people are coming into the hospital (Admissions) versus how many people are healthy enough to go home (Discharges). This helps the hospital manage its space.

3. Department Breakdown
This part of the page uses colorful charts to show which parts of the hospital are the busiest. For example, it might show that the Emergency Room is full while the Physiotherapy department is quiet. This helps managers move staff to where they are needed most.

4. Patient Satisfaction
Often, this page includes a small section showing "Patient Ratings" or "Wait Times." It tells the hospital if the patients are happy with the care they are receiving and if they are being seen quickly enough.

5. Time Trends
A simple line graph usually shows the "Pulse" of the hospital over the last 24 hours or the last week. It shows when the "rush hours" happen so the hospital can prepare for them in the future.
